<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-04"><hi rend="italic">May 4,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegraphic orders sent Cuba suspending all executive action until
                            examination can be made as to all taken upon <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi> who may prove to be American citizens.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>